    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="656"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.24/7–1941</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Adviser on Political Relations</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hornbeck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-19">July 19,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Welles</hi>: There were three parts to the program of
                    action which I suggested in my memorandum of yesterday<note n="93"
                        xml:id="d656fn93">Memorandum not found in Department files.</note> regarding
                    action to be taken when Japanese action in and against Indochina becomes
                    obvious: namely, economic pressures and, simultaneously with the application
                    thereof, expedition of additional aid to China and new disposals of armed forces
                    (especially planes) in the Far East (especially at Manila). I hope that none of
                    the three will be overlooked and that all three of these measures will be taken
                    simultaneously.</p>
            </div>
